=> The Throwable class is the superclass of all errors and exceptions in the Java language.

Throwable(root-class)
	- Error(it is not recoverable): memory leaks, out of memory and stack overflow error..etc.
	- Exception(it is recoverable): IOExceptions, SQLExceptions, RuntimeException and NullPointerException..etc.
	
Types of Exceptions:
	
	- Predefined Exceptions: these all exceptions are the part of java libraries.
		- Checked Exceptions: except RuntimeException and Its Subclasses, remaining all are checked exceptions 
		
		- Unchecked Exceptions: Error and RuntimeException and Its Subclasses are unchecked exceptions
	
	- User-Defined Exceptions: these type of exceptions we are going to create based on our need.